  "prompt": "How do you clean a penny board?",
  "response": "Cleaning a Penny Board is a straightforward process that helps maintain its appearance and longevity. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n### What You\u2019ll Need:\n- Mild dish soap\n- Warm water\n- Soft sponge or cloth\n- Toothbrush or small brush\n- Microfiber towel or clean cloth\n- Isopropyl alcohol (optional for deep cleaning)\n- Wax or protective spray (optional)\n\n---\n\n### Steps to Clean Your Penny Board:\n\n1. **Remove the Wheels and Bearings**:\n   - Use a skate tool or wrench to remove the wheels.\n   - Take out the bearings if you want to clean them separately (bearings can be cleaned with isopropyl alcohol).\n\n2. **Wipe Down the Deck**:\n   - Use a damp cloth or sponge with warm water and a small amount of mild dish soap to wipe down the deck.\n   - Avoid soaking the board, as water can seep into the plastic and weaken it.\n\n3. **Scrub the Grip Tape (if applicable)**:\n   - If your Penny Board has grip tape, use a toothbrush or small brush to remove dirt and debris.\n   - For stubborn grime, lightly scrape the surface with a grip tape eraser or the edge of a plastic card.\n\n4. **Clean the Wheels and Trucks**:\n   - Use soapy water and a brush to clean the wheels and trucks.\n   - For stubborn dirt, use a small amount of isopropyl alcohol on a cloth.\n\n5. **Dry Thoroughly**:\n   - Use a microfiber towel or clean cloth to dry the deck, wheels, and trucks completely.\n   - Ensure all parts are dry before reassembling to prevent rust or damage.\n\n6. **(Optional) Apply Wax or Protective Spray**:\n   - After cleaning, you can apply a plastic protectant or wax to the deck to restore shine and protect it from UV damage.\n\n7. **Reassemble the Board**:\n   - Put the bearings back into the wheels (if removed) and reattach the wheels to the trucks.\n   - Ensure all bolts are tightened securely.\n\n---\n\n### Tips:\n- Avoid using harsh chemicals or abrasive cleaners, as they can damage the plastic and components.\n- Clean your board regularly, especially after riding in wet or dirty conditions.\n- Store your Penny Board in a cool, dry place to prevent warping or discoloration.\n\nBy following these steps, your Penny Board will stay clean and look great for years to come!",
